article.headline: Princeton 75, Harvard 48
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Kyle Koncz scored 23 points to lead Princeton to a 75-48 win over Harvard on Saturday night. Scott Greenman added 11 points and six assists for Princeton (10-14, 8-4 in Ivy League, while Justin Conway had 10 points and four assists. Jim Goffredo led Harvard (12-13, 4-8) with 14 points and had the Crimson's lone 3-pointer on a night where they struggled from the floor and committed 13 turnovers. Matt Stehle and Michael Beal added eight points each. Princeton, which held several double-digit leads during the game, took command early on and hit nine 3-pointers in the first half to jump out to a 37-19 lead at the break. They continued their domination in the second half as their defense continued to stymie Harvard, which hit just 45 percent of its shots. Meanwhile, the Tigers were on fire most of the night, hitting 62.5 percent of their shots overall and going 13-for-19 from 3-point range.
